    <h2>Microbiological Figures</h2>
    <p>It was during my PhD in microbiology that I found a love for designing and making data visualisations, where figures are essential for conveying the results. I greatly enjoyed putting due consideration into the look and feel of my figures, as in my opinion there's really nothing worse than an ugly looking graph.</p>
    <p>Here, I show a selection of my favourite figures, taken from:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>My thesis, titled "The effects of subinhibitory antibiotic concentrations on
        <em>Pseudomonas&nbsp;aeruginosa</em>
        within model Cystic Fibrosis bacterial communities";</li>
      <li>My subsequent published paper, titled "The Effects of Antibiotic Combination Treatments on
        <em>Pseudomonas aeruginosa</em>
        Tolerance Evolution and Coexistence with
        <em>Stenotrophomonas maltophilia</em>".</li>
      <ul>
        <li><a href='https://dx.doi.org/10.1128/spectrum.01842-22'>(Law, Wood & Friman.&nbsp;<em>Microbiol Spectr.</em>&nbsp;2022;&nbsp;10(6):e0184222)</a></li>
      </ul>
    </ul>
    <p>Click the images to see the full figure and read a small commentary on each.</p>
  </section>
